attribute.name: DESCRIPTION
attribute.valueCLOB:
Overview

Raising capital to finance business expansion or working capital requires financing solutions considerate of a business's specific circumstances and needs. Term loans can provide the ideal vehicle for providing such debt funding, as they can be customised to each client's unique requirements while at the same time offering simplicity and cost-effectiveness.
 

Why talk to us?

  • Our specialist team combines relevant sector expertise with a detailed understanding of your business, collaborating with other specialist units in the bank to provide the most appropriate debt solution to meet your funding objectives.
  • Standard Bank's focus on emerging markets globally, and our presence in key markets around the world, enables us to offer competitive cross-border solutions in various currencies.
  • Our distribution channels, both locally and through our London-based syndication desk, means we are well placed as both a funding arranger and as a participant in broader bank syndication offerings.

Products and services

Lending facilities with tenors longer than three months are structured to meet our clients' specific funding requirements, and to address issues relevant to a particular counterparty. Although each structured facility is different, some of the more common variations include:

  • Specific project funding for working capital / bridging purposes
  • Revolving or fixed drawdown and repayment arrangements
  • Bullet or amortising repayment profiles
  • Secured or unsecured funding
  • Variable or fixed interest rates

contentInstance.vcmName: Mark Fox joins Standard Bank's FIC Sales Team

attribute.name: TITLE
attribute.valueString: Mark Fox joins Standard Bank's FIC Sales Team

attribute.name: INTRODUCTION
attribute.valueString: Mark Fox has joined Standard Banks Fixed Income and Currency (FIC) Sales team in the Global Markets division as Head of London Buyside, he will be based in London. Mark will report to Guido Haller, Global Head of Global Markets Clients and regionally to Ian Dalglish, Head of Global Markets International.

attribute.name: DESCRIPTION
attribute.valueCLOB:
Mark Fox has joined Standard Bank's Fixed Income and Currency (FIC) Sales team in the Global Markets division as Head of London Buyside, he will be based in London. Mark will report to Guido Haller, Global Head of Global Markets Clients and regionally to Ian Dalglish, Head of Global Markets International. 

In this role, Mark will be responsible for serving the European specialist emerging markets fixed income client base, including large hedge funds and real money accounts in every European country.

Mark joins Standard Bank from Jefferies, where he was European Head of Emerging Market Fixed Income Sales. Mark has previously worked at UBS and at Lehman Brothers where he was Chief Strategist; he brings with him over 2 decades of experience.

Mark is a former lecturer and examiner in Emerging Markets for the International Securities Markets Association at the University of Reading and has written articles on emerging markets in a range of publications.

Guido Haller commented, "Mark brings strong sales experience and a sound knowledge of Emerging Markets to Standard Bank's FIC team. His appointment will strengthen our relationship with a number of key clients, diversify our product placement and ensure that Standard Bank is the counterparty of choice in our markets"

Ian Dalglish added, "With Mark's appointment we look forward to continuing to provide the highest level of service, product offerings and innovative investment solutions to our clients."
